description: After a quick dinner that's big on flavour? Follow this easy fried rice recipe with our one-tray hack. It's a flavour-packed meal ready in just 20 minutes.
keywords: Fried rice,High fibre,High protein,Seafood free,Tree nut free,Traybake,Low sugar,Sesame free,Dairy free,Jul 2021
name: Fried rice traybake Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 350g lup chong (Chinese pork sausages), thinly sliced diagonally
1 cup frozen mixed carrot, peas and corn

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Drizzle oil over a 26 x 30cm (3cm deep) baking tray. Place lup chong, frozen vegetables and half the onion in tray. Stir to combine. Bake for 5 minutes or until vegetables have softened.
Add rice and soy sauce to tray, stirring to combine.
Using back of a spoon, make 4 indentations in rice mixture.
Crack an egg into each indentation, then bake for a further 10 minutes or until egg is cooked. Scatter over remaining onion. Serve.
